news.title: Sushma group raises Rs 100 crore from Motilal Oswal
news.para: The fund will also be used to give exit to existing lender LIC housing and remaining will be used to complete the construction of project.

news.title: Germany and Austria told to curb boom in home prices
news.para: "Austria and Germany...had already received ESRB warnings in 2016 and 2019, respectively (but their) vulnerabilities have not been addressed sufficiently," the ESRB said.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Income tax department finds Rs 7 crore cash, gold in searches on builders
news.para: The raids started on Thursday on Shilp, Shivalik and Sharda Developers by teams comprising 50 officers and 100 staff members from across Gujarat.

news.title: No increase in property tax in North Delhi civic body's budget
news.para: There was also no increase in property tax. Goswami accepted that in the last decade South MCD has not paid rent worth Rs 2,833 crores to North MCD but failed to explain why it happened.

news.title: No discrimination against any state on allotment of houses under PMAY-G: Government
news.para: ​Replying to queries raised by Lok Sabha members regarding the scheme, he also clarified that Karnataka was allowed to enter beneficiaries data in the Awaas Plus portal for allotment of houses as it had not received any such houses.

news.title: Telangana government to auction 1,400 open plots in nine districts
news.para: To begin with, the government will auction 1,400 open plots in 9 districts. The land auction will be held in physical mode from March 14 to 17, as per the notification issued on Friday.

news.title: Emaar row: Telangana HC dismisses plea by 75 buyers seeking return of plots
news.para: The petitioners cited the controversy surrounding Emaar and sought restitution of their rights over land. While rejecting the demand, the court also questioned why the petitioners approached the court 15 years after the land acquisition in 2002.

news.title: Bank loses Bengaluru man's property papers, ordered to pay Rs 25,000
news.para: In a recent judgment, the forum ruled the bank must furnish a certified copy of the documents and pay the man a compensation of Rs 25,000 for deficiency in service.

news.title: Gurugram civic body declares 80 buildings unsafe
news.para: In fact, a total of 183 buildings were identified as unsafe or dangerous structures by a private firm contracted by the MCG during the recent property tax assessment survey.

news.title: Gurugram: 35 Chintels Paradiso families became homeless overnight
news.para: Around 35 families with houses in other floors of Tower D spent the night at friends’, neighbours’ or relatives’ homes as the tower was sealed. With not even a change of clothes with them, they said they have become refugees overnight.

news.title: ADIA-backed Lake Shore acquires Viviana Mall from Ashwin Sheth, GIC for Rs 1,900 crore
news.para: The acquisition of the operational retail property is also this year’s first single-largest real estate transaction in the country.

news.title: Call grows for structural audit in high-rises in Noida
news.para: The Noida Authority, however, maintains that the responsibility for such audits lies with the RWAs/AOAs of the society once the occupation certificate (OC) has been issued by the authority.

news.title: Gurugram: Jitters in other societies, calls grow for system to ensure structural audits
news.para: Many residents of societies in the new sectors said they had lodged several complaints about construction quality in their towers and chunks and plasters falling off the ceilings.

news.title: Sebi bars Reliance Home Finance, Anil Ambani, others from securities market
news.para: In a 100-page interim order, the regulator also restrained the individuals from "associating themselves with any intermediary registered with Sebi, any listed public company or acting directors/ promoters of any public company which intends to raise money from the public till further orders."

news.title: Sobha's profit up 51% to Rs 32.7 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income rose marginally to Rs 697.5 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal, from Rs 696.3 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.Total income rose marginally to Rs 697.5 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal, from Rs 696.3 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.
